    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-30T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-30T14:00:00-05:00" n="310"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d310">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 103.97/60</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Special Representative</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_HEM1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">House</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-30T19:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 30, 1917, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received December 1, 12.55 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Our 25. For <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_HHC1">Hoover</persName> from
                        <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_TAE1">Taylor</persName>:</p>
                <p>Swiss not to receive wheat from you. Other neutrals the same. Marked reduction in
                    cereal rations are to be introduced by Allies. They need from market [<hi
                        rend="italic">North America</hi>] during December, January and February
                    [1,]100,000 tons of mixed cereals per month, then they draw from Argentina and
                    India. Argentine wheat must be secured.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_HEM1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Edward House</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
